theorem interior_closure_interior_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior (closure (interior (closure (A : Set X)))) =
      interior (closure (A : Set X)) := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- `⊆` direction
    have h :
        closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := by
      apply closure_mono
      exact interior_subset (s := closure (A : Set X))
    exact interior_mono h
  · -- `⊇` direction
    have h :
        interior (closure (A : Set X)) ⊆
          interior (closure (interior (closure (A : Set X)))) := by
      apply interior_maximal
      · -- `interior (closure A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A))`
        exact subset_closure
      · -- `interior (closure A)` is open
        exact isOpen_interior
    exact h

theorem P1_of_dense_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA : closure (interior (A : Set X)) = Set.univ) :
    Topology.P1 A := by
  dsimp [Topology.P1]
  intro x hx
  have : (x : X) ∈ (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simp
  simpa [hA] using this
